1
00:01:04,152 --> 00:01:06,988
QUEEN OF TEARS

2
00:01:08,198 --> 00:01:09,908
Du-gwan!

3
00:01:09,991 --> 00:01:11,743
Look!

4
00:01:12,202 --> 00:01:13,036
Oh, dear!

5
00:01:13,119 --> 00:01:14,871
FORMER CEO HONG HAE-IN TERMINALLY ILL

6
00:01:17,582 --> 00:01:19,292
-Gosh!
-Gosh, Du-gwan!

7
00:01:19,375 --> 00:01:20,460
Du-gwan!

8
00:01:20,543 --> 00:01:22,045
Don't forget your shoes!

9
00:01:22,128 --> 00:01:23,213
Mi-seon!

10
00:01:32,514 --> 00:01:35,475
Because I was told

11
00:01:37,185 --> 00:01:38,520
that I have little time left…

12
00:01:39,270 --> 00:01:40,355
to live.

13
00:01:46,820 --> 00:01:48,571
When were you diagnosed?

14
00:01:48,655 --> 00:01:50,740
Is Chairman Yoon aware of this too?

15
00:03:17,869 --> 00:03:19,829
Hae-in.

16
00:03:22,123 --> 00:03:22,999
I can't die yet.

17
00:03:25,293 --> 00:03:26,586
I haven't

18
00:03:27,545 --> 00:03:29,297
told you yet.

19
00:03:30,506 --> 00:03:31,799
Moving through!

20
00:03:34,427 --> 00:03:35,345
That it's okay.

21
00:03:40,099 --> 00:03:42,685
That I never resented you.

22
00:03:43,186 --> 00:03:44,604
What's the use of it?

23
00:03:44,687 --> 00:03:45,939
It only gets on my nerves.

24
00:03:47,315 --> 00:03:49,692
Let's part ways. I want a divorce.

25
00:03:50,568 --> 00:03:53,488
I haven't thanked you
for being by my side all these years…

26
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:04,624
despite all the harsh words

27
00:04:05,208 --> 00:04:06,292
I didn't mean.

28
00:04:06,376 --> 00:04:08,294
I love her.

29
00:04:12,257 --> 00:04:13,841
I love you, Hae-in.

30
00:04:16,261 --> 00:04:17,470
I love you.

31
00:04:20,181 --> 00:04:22,767
You were the reason
I wanted to live even more.

32
00:04:22,850 --> 00:04:23,768
You can't come in.

33
00:04:23,851 --> 00:04:25,728
You're not allowed to come inside.

34
00:04:33,653 --> 00:04:35,822
I thought I had more time.

35
00:05:40,762 --> 00:05:42,930
We're looking for Hong Hae-in.

36
00:05:44,265 --> 00:05:46,809
Ma'am, where's Hong Hae-in?

37
00:05:47,810 --> 00:05:50,229
I haven't apologized to everyone yet.

38
00:05:55,276 --> 00:05:58,905
INTENSIVE CARE UNIT

39
00:06:27,392 --> 00:06:28,559
I'm sorry.

40
00:06:36,776 --> 00:06:38,277
I'm sorry for everything.

41
00:06:45,785 --> 00:06:46,911
EPISODE 11

42
00:07:02,677 --> 00:07:04,011
I thought you hadn't found him.

43
00:07:05,054 --> 00:07:06,681
-You see--
-Get out.

44
00:07:08,349 --> 00:07:11,102
What gives you the right?
This isn't your hospital.

45
00:07:11,185 --> 00:07:15,106
You're going to see the chairman.
Get out since I won't let you.

46
00:07:15,189 --> 00:07:18,651
Your son betrayed you and moved him here.

47
00:07:18,734 --> 00:07:21,779
So do you still think
that you're his legal guardian?

48
00:07:21,863 --> 00:07:23,656
Do you think I'd let that slide?

49
00:07:26,242 --> 00:07:28,744
I'll get out myself.

50
00:07:36,252 --> 00:07:37,253
Damn it.

51
00:07:39,046 --> 00:07:41,424
Hey! Damn it!

52
00:07:45,511 --> 00:07:46,554
Hey!

53
00:08:00,860 --> 00:08:01,736
EMERGENCY STAIRCASE

54
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:18,169
-Open the door.
-I'm sorry, but I can't do that.

55
00:08:18,252 --> 00:08:19,837
I wasn't talking to you. Open it.

56
00:08:26,302 --> 00:08:27,428
Me too!

57
00:08:28,346 --> 00:08:29,722
Let me in too!

58
00:08:29,805 --> 00:08:32,975
Look. I'm begging you.

59
00:08:33,059 --> 00:08:36,687
Please. I'm sorry for being
so rude to you all this time.

60
00:08:36,771 --> 00:08:38,189
Please forgive me.

61
00:08:39,023 --> 00:08:42,818
Please let me see my father
just this once.

62
00:08:42,902 --> 00:08:43,819
Please.

63
00:08:44,445 --> 00:08:45,696
Should I kneel?

64
00:08:46,322 --> 00:08:47,156
Should I?

65
00:08:47,657 --> 00:08:48,658
Fine.

66
00:08:49,367 --> 00:08:50,785
Fine? Really?

67
00:08:52,245 --> 00:08:53,538
Do you mean that?

68
00:08:55,456 --> 00:08:59,210
But I want you to leave right afterward.
If not, you'll be dragged out.

69
00:09:00,670 --> 00:09:04,006
Thank you.

70
00:09:22,233 --> 00:09:23,317
Father?

71
00:09:27,113 --> 00:09:29,031
Father!

72
00:09:29,657 --> 00:09:30,908
Father!

73
00:09:30,992 --> 00:09:33,160
Father!

74
00:09:33,244 --> 00:09:36,122
You woke up!

75
00:09:36,205 --> 00:09:38,708
I'm so proud of you!

76
00:09:38,791 --> 00:09:40,668
You did well!

77
00:09:48,134 --> 00:09:50,177
Come on, now.

78
00:09:50,261 --> 00:09:52,680
Don't you know who I am?

79
00:09:55,099 --> 00:09:56,767
Jeez.

80
00:09:56,851 --> 00:09:58,352
Father!

81
00:09:58,436 --> 00:10:00,896
What? Did he pass away?

82
00:10:02,106 --> 00:10:03,733
Father!

83
00:10:04,942 --> 00:10:08,946
Father!

84
00:10:19,915 --> 00:10:21,208
You bitch.

85
00:10:22,043 --> 00:10:23,919
You're done for.

86
00:10:24,003 --> 00:10:26,505
So he made you his legal guardian?

87
00:10:26,589 --> 00:10:28,174
He's awake now.

88
00:10:28,257 --> 00:10:31,802
So you've lost the power
of attorney now. Am I right?

89
00:10:32,428 --> 00:10:34,263
Yes, that's true.

90
00:10:35,139 --> 00:10:38,059
-Wait. Let's call his doctor--
-Shut up!

91
00:10:39,018 --> 00:10:40,811
Call the police.

92
00:10:42,021 --> 00:10:42,855
Father.

93
00:10:43,731 --> 00:10:45,566
It was her, wasn't it?

94
00:10:45,650 --> 00:10:48,277
That bitch harmed you, didn't she?

95
00:11:01,666 --> 00:11:03,000
Who are you?

96
00:11:16,597 --> 00:11:17,640
Father…

97
00:11:46,335 --> 00:11:47,753
Damn it!

98
00:11:48,295 --> 00:11:49,880
Why are you kicking me out too?

99
00:11:51,590 --> 00:11:52,591
Damn it.

100
00:12:00,850 --> 00:12:04,854
INTENSIVE CARE UNIT

101
00:12:17,950 --> 00:12:21,120
What's… wrong with her?

102
00:12:22,455 --> 00:12:23,372
Mother…

103
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:26,834
What's her problem?

104
00:12:26,917 --> 00:12:30,504
The CT scan shows acute brain swelling.

105
00:12:30,588 --> 00:12:32,882
The brain tumor cells pressured
the surrounding tissues

106
00:12:32,965 --> 00:12:35,259
and temporarily increased
her intracranial pressure.

107
00:12:35,342 --> 00:12:36,510
We should lower it first--

108
00:12:36,594 --> 00:12:38,471
Brain tumor?

109
00:12:38,554 --> 00:12:39,972
What do you mean?

110
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:46,103
Were you aware of everything
Hae-in announced? Is that so?

111
00:12:46,187 --> 00:12:49,273
-Honey.
-Then why didn't you tell us? Why?

112
00:12:49,356 --> 00:12:50,858
What have you been doing?

113
00:12:50,941 --> 00:12:53,277
You should've told us that she was sick.

114
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:54,236
Why didn't you?

115
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,780
-Stop.
-He deceived us again!

116
00:13:00,034 --> 00:13:01,869
He kept it a secret from us.

117
00:13:01,952 --> 00:13:04,330
He deceived us
when Hae-in was this severely ill.

118
00:13:04,413 --> 00:13:07,082
-What are you scheming this time?
-I told you to stop.

119
00:13:12,254 --> 00:13:13,923
We have no right to get upset.

120
00:13:23,015 --> 00:13:24,016
I'm sorry.

121
00:13:25,351 --> 00:13:27,061
We had no idea

122
00:13:27,770 --> 00:13:29,855
despite being her parents.

123
00:13:31,148 --> 00:13:32,191
Please explain.

124
00:13:33,526 --> 00:13:34,985
Please elaborate

125
00:13:36,195 --> 00:13:39,323
on her current condition.

126
00:13:40,032 --> 00:13:43,953
Ms. Hong is suffering from Cloud Cytoma.

127
00:13:44,036 --> 00:13:46,121
It's a type of malignant brain tumor.

128
00:13:46,914 --> 00:13:50,584
Unlike your typical tumor,
where the tumor is

129
00:13:50,668 --> 00:13:52,044
a big lump,

130
00:13:52,127 --> 00:13:55,798
these tumor cells have spread
throughout her cranial nerves like clouds.

131
00:13:55,881 --> 00:13:59,468
Her case is a very rare one worldwide,

132
00:14:00,261 --> 00:14:02,221
so it's been difficult to treat her.

133
00:14:14,859 --> 00:14:16,443
I'm sorry, Mother.

134
00:14:50,185 --> 00:14:53,564
I'm truly sorry
that I didn't tell you sooner.

135
00:14:53,647 --> 00:14:55,858
She probably told you not to.

136
00:14:56,942 --> 00:14:58,736
It must've been a great burden.

137
00:15:04,033 --> 00:15:06,493
Hae-in didn't want her parents

138
00:15:06,577 --> 00:15:08,370
to be heartbroken.

139
00:15:08,454 --> 00:15:11,832
So she wanted to tell you
once things were looking up.

140
00:15:13,167 --> 00:15:15,544
I hope you don't get the wrong idea.

141
00:15:38,275 --> 00:15:39,401
Dad.

142
00:15:46,450 --> 00:15:49,954
By the vast and endless ocean

143
00:15:50,037 --> 00:15:53,749
Stood a single humble cottage

144
00:15:53,832 --> 00:15:57,044
Dwelt a fisherman father

145
00:15:57,127 --> 00:16:00,547
And his young daughter

146
00:16:00,631 --> 00:16:03,801
Oh my love, oh my love

147
00:16:03,884 --> 00:16:06,929
Oh my love, Clementine

148
00:16:07,012 --> 00:16:10,432
Why have you abandoned me forever

149
00:16:10,516 --> 00:16:13,352
Leaving your old father behind

150
00:16:26,907 --> 00:16:28,325
Judging by the MRI results,

151
00:16:28,409 --> 00:16:31,495
I believe he has vascular dementia
due to a head injury and brain hemorrhage.

152
00:16:31,578 --> 00:16:33,914
The significant damage
to his frontal and temporal lobes

153
00:16:33,998 --> 00:16:37,042
is making it difficult for him
to think rationally or remember things.

154
00:16:37,126 --> 00:16:42,506
For now, we have no choice
but to wait until his brain recovers.

155
00:16:42,589 --> 00:16:44,299
Let's give him two weeks.

156
00:16:44,383 --> 00:16:46,093
Does that mean he could recover?

157
00:16:46,176 --> 00:16:49,054
It varies per case,
so I can't guarantee anything.

158
00:17:17,291 --> 00:17:18,125
Seon-hwa.

159
00:17:21,170 --> 00:17:22,004
You must be stunned.

160
00:17:23,047 --> 00:17:25,049
I just heard and--

161
00:17:25,132 --> 00:17:26,925
You knew she was sick.

162
00:17:28,469 --> 00:17:31,346
That's why you told me
not to do things I'd regret.

163
00:17:36,769 --> 00:17:37,936
I'm sorry.

164
00:17:42,107 --> 00:17:43,776
Everyone knew.

165
00:17:44,985 --> 00:17:46,487
Everyone knew but me.

166
00:17:51,450 --> 00:17:52,409
But, Mom,

167
00:17:53,494 --> 00:17:56,747
I just told you
that I had a serious matter too.

168
00:17:57,831 --> 00:17:59,291
Aren't you curious?

169
00:17:59,374 --> 00:18:03,128
You always know what to do
whether it's big or small.

170
00:18:03,796 --> 00:18:04,797
Right.

171
00:18:06,048 --> 00:18:07,257
I'll take care

172
00:18:08,383 --> 00:18:09,468
of my business.

173
00:18:12,262 --> 00:18:14,681
Jeez, don't be so dramatic.

174
00:18:14,765 --> 00:18:16,100
I'm anemic too.

175
00:18:16,183 --> 00:18:19,061
I'm also dizzy
since I couldn't sleep much either.

176
00:18:19,144 --> 00:18:21,605
It's not like Soo-cheol
is doing fine either.

177
00:18:22,314 --> 00:18:23,607
We're all suffering here.

178
00:20:03,916 --> 00:20:05,417
-What?
-What is this about Hae-in?

179
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:07,711
Is it true? Is she sick?

180
00:20:07,794 --> 00:20:09,171
I doubt her family knew.

181
00:20:09,254 --> 00:20:10,714
Not even Soo-cheol.

182
00:20:10,797 --> 00:20:12,299
He must be shocked.

183
00:20:17,221 --> 00:20:18,805
That's why you called?

184
00:20:18,889 --> 00:20:20,098
It's a small favor.

185
00:20:20,724 --> 00:20:24,102
He has anxiety disorder.
It happens when he's stressed.

186
00:20:24,186 --> 00:20:26,313
It's serious. He needs medication.

187
00:20:26,396 --> 00:20:28,523
I don't think he took any with him.

188
00:20:28,607 --> 00:20:32,069
We have some at home.
Can you tell someone to get it?

189
00:20:32,152 --> 00:20:33,195
-It's--
-Hey.

190
00:20:33,278 --> 00:20:36,031
-Cheon Da-hye.
-He might faint and die!

191
00:20:36,114 --> 00:20:38,784
-Then let him die.
-Hey, how could you…

192
00:20:40,202 --> 00:20:41,745
What do you want me to do?

193
00:20:42,412 --> 00:20:43,872
Should I kill him?

194
00:20:44,414 --> 00:20:46,667
Don't ever call me again
over something like this!

195
00:20:47,709 --> 00:20:49,336
Or I'll kill him myself.

196
00:21:01,348 --> 00:21:02,182
Hyun-woo.

197
00:21:07,896 --> 00:21:09,147
I think this was why.

198
00:21:10,023 --> 00:21:11,024
What do you mean?

199
00:21:15,028 --> 00:21:16,280
What is that?

200
00:21:16,780 --> 00:21:18,699
I was told to carry this around…

201
00:21:21,451 --> 00:21:23,161
so it'd subdue her energy.

202
00:21:23,787 --> 00:21:25,372
I didn't believe it.

203
00:21:26,581 --> 00:21:28,959
I just wanted
to be better than her for once.

204
00:21:30,669 --> 00:21:31,878
But…

205
00:21:32,838 --> 00:21:34,506
what if this damn talisman

206
00:21:34,589 --> 00:21:39,386
is the reason why she's sick?

207
00:21:40,387 --> 00:21:41,763
It's all my fault.

208
00:21:41,847 --> 00:21:44,224
I shouldn't have carried
this stupid talisman.

209
00:22:05,078 --> 00:22:06,079
Hae-in.

210
00:22:06,997 --> 00:22:08,123
Hae-in!

211
00:22:12,669 --> 00:22:15,172
What about a talisman? You lunatic.

212
00:22:18,592 --> 00:22:22,262
Did you see that?
This talisman must be powerful.

213
00:22:22,346 --> 00:22:24,431
She woke up once I ripped it up.

214
00:22:25,474 --> 00:22:26,391
Soo-cheol.

215
00:22:27,601 --> 00:22:29,311
I'm sorry…

216
00:22:31,521 --> 00:22:32,356
for everything.

217
00:22:34,524 --> 00:22:38,236
Hyun-woo, I don't think
she's in her right mind.

218
00:22:40,655 --> 00:22:42,282
Go get the doctor and the family.

219
00:22:42,366 --> 00:22:43,450
Our family…

220
00:22:58,465 --> 00:23:00,217
-Are you okay?
-I love you.

221
00:23:04,096 --> 00:23:05,847
I've loved you

222
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:07,849
from the moment we met

223
00:23:09,309 --> 00:23:10,143
until now.

224
00:23:13,688 --> 00:23:16,108
I'm sorry that I didn't treat you better.

225
00:23:17,567 --> 00:23:19,986
I'm also sorry that I left you all alone

226
00:23:21,780 --> 00:23:22,614
with my family.

227
00:23:25,158 --> 00:23:27,661
I think a part of me already knew

228
00:23:28,995 --> 00:23:30,288
that you wanted a divorce.

229
00:23:33,375 --> 00:23:34,918
You put up with us for so long.

230
00:23:35,001 --> 00:23:36,211
So…

231
00:23:37,754 --> 00:23:39,881
it's okay. Don't feel bad.

232
00:23:48,306 --> 00:23:49,433
What are you doing?

233
00:23:50,183 --> 00:23:52,310
If I don't say these things before I die,

234
00:23:54,187 --> 00:23:56,815
you'll never know how I really feel.

235
00:23:59,818 --> 00:24:01,153
I'm telling you this now

236
00:24:02,863 --> 00:24:04,406
since I don't know when I'll die.

237
00:24:20,922 --> 00:24:22,257
Last night,

238
00:24:24,301 --> 00:24:26,845
I prayed
more than I had done in my entire life.

239
00:24:30,265 --> 00:24:32,058
I said I'd do nothing,

240
00:24:33,351 --> 00:24:35,020
but cry every day,

241
00:24:36,438 --> 00:24:37,689
drink a ton of alcohol,

242
00:24:39,024 --> 00:24:40,108
sleep on the street,

243
00:24:41,318 --> 00:24:42,861
and live recklessly

244
00:24:44,529 --> 00:24:45,906
if you died.

245
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:51,661
That's a threat, not a prayer.

246
00:24:58,585 --> 00:24:59,669
I don't care.

247
00:25:01,046 --> 00:25:02,422
If you die,

248
00:25:04,508 --> 00:25:05,842
I'll give up on myself.

249
00:25:05,926 --> 00:25:06,927
You just watch.

250
00:25:07,010 --> 00:25:08,845
How can I watch when I'm dead?

251
00:25:09,471 --> 00:25:11,306
So cut the nonsense.

252
00:25:12,182 --> 00:25:13,767
I'm opening my heart to you.

253
00:25:17,062 --> 00:25:18,188
I was even scared

254
00:25:18,939 --> 00:25:20,982
in my sleep in case I wouldn't be able

255
00:25:22,150 --> 00:25:23,360
to tell you.

256
00:25:25,529 --> 00:25:26,613
Don't be scared.

257
00:25:28,907 --> 00:25:30,325
You're not going to die.

258
00:25:39,292 --> 00:25:40,919
You won't die.

259
00:25:42,879 --> 00:25:44,256
I won't let you.

260
00:26:03,650 --> 00:26:05,110
ENDOSCOPY

261
00:26:05,193 --> 00:26:06,486
Mom!

262
00:26:06,570 --> 00:26:08,947
Hae-in woke up! Hurry up!

263
00:26:26,631 --> 00:26:28,466
Where did she go?

264
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:33,346
Why didn't you tell us about this?

265
00:26:33,972 --> 00:26:36,391
But it's okay. I know about it now.

266
00:26:37,017 --> 00:26:40,979
Don't worry. Many of my close friends
are renown doctors.

267
00:26:41,062 --> 00:26:42,606
They're all around the world.

268
00:26:42,689 --> 00:26:45,650
Is that so? I should've told you sooner.

269
00:26:51,740 --> 00:26:52,574
I'm sorry.

270
00:26:55,994 --> 00:26:59,456
Why are you sorry?
You're the one who's sick.

271
00:27:00,081 --> 00:27:02,834
You should've told me sooner.

272
00:27:02,917 --> 00:27:05,462
It must've been so painful
to keep it a secret.

273
00:27:06,671 --> 00:27:08,298
You're okay now.

274
00:27:09,466 --> 00:27:11,426
Everything will be fine. Okay?

275
00:27:11,509 --> 00:27:12,344
Okay.

276
00:27:20,602 --> 00:27:21,645
Where's Mom?

277
00:27:40,372 --> 00:27:41,247
Mother.

278
00:27:42,332 --> 00:27:44,292
Let me be alone.

279
00:27:44,376 --> 00:27:47,420
I'm truly sorry that I didn't tell you

280
00:27:48,380 --> 00:27:49,422
sooner.

281
00:27:51,549 --> 00:27:52,467
Forget it.

282
00:27:53,218 --> 00:27:54,803
What kind of mother

283
00:27:56,221 --> 00:27:58,515
doesn't know that her child is dying?

284
00:27:59,224 --> 00:28:01,685
I know nothing about my own daughter.

285
00:28:08,274 --> 00:28:09,442
How pathetic.

286
00:28:09,901 --> 00:28:12,404
I can't believe I took my pain out

287
00:28:12,487 --> 00:28:14,906
on my own daughter.

288
00:28:17,492 --> 00:28:19,619
Whenever that young child
reached out to me…

289
00:28:24,332 --> 00:28:25,166
I didn't hold her

290
00:28:26,835 --> 00:28:28,336
even once.

291
00:28:43,560 --> 00:28:45,311
Even I can't live with myself.

292
00:28:45,979 --> 00:28:47,897
I'd hate to have a mom like me.

293
00:28:54,070 --> 00:28:55,029
Hyun-woo.

294
00:28:56,322 --> 00:28:57,991
It's all my fault.

295
00:28:58,074 --> 00:29:00,744
I caused my daughter

296
00:29:01,369 --> 00:29:04,164
pain and stress.

297
00:29:05,623 --> 00:29:07,375
That's why she's sick.

298
00:29:29,439 --> 00:29:30,815
Are you a doctor?

299
00:29:37,822 --> 00:29:40,700
How could you know things
that a doctor doesn't even know?

300
00:29:41,451 --> 00:29:45,038
They don't know the cause
or how to prevent my illness.

301
00:29:45,121 --> 00:29:47,874
It's not caused by stress either.

302
00:29:47,957 --> 00:29:49,417
How are you…

303
00:29:56,132 --> 00:29:57,425
so naive?

304
00:29:58,676 --> 00:30:00,011
You're so annoying.

305
00:30:04,849 --> 00:30:05,683
And…

306
00:30:08,603 --> 00:30:09,646
I would've struggled

307
00:30:11,231 --> 00:30:12,816
to have a daughter like me too.

308
00:30:13,566 --> 00:30:14,984
So it's not all your fault.

309
00:30:16,486 --> 00:30:17,320
Hae-in.

310
00:30:37,966 --> 00:30:39,133
Did it hurt

311
00:30:40,468 --> 00:30:41,928
a lot?

312
00:30:48,059 --> 00:30:49,394
Well…

313
00:30:50,228 --> 00:30:53,314
There were times when it hurt
and times when it didn't.

314
00:30:59,529 --> 00:31:01,739
I had no idea you were sick.

315
00:31:02,782 --> 00:31:03,867
I'm sorry.

316
00:31:05,118 --> 00:31:06,369
It's all my fault.

317
00:31:07,495 --> 00:31:09,497
I'm sorry.

318
00:31:10,248 --> 00:31:12,000
I was wrong.

319
00:31:14,085 --> 00:31:15,461
I told you.

320
00:31:16,254 --> 00:31:19,340
This has nothing to do
with how you treated me.

321
00:31:19,424 --> 00:31:21,593
I didn't want to tell you because I knew

322
00:31:24,429 --> 00:31:25,972
you wouldn't understand.

323
00:31:29,767 --> 00:31:30,602
I'm sorry.

324
00:31:31,394 --> 00:31:32,395
I'm…

325
00:31:33,021 --> 00:31:35,023
I'm really sorry.

326
00:31:36,941 --> 00:31:38,151
I can't live

327
00:31:39,277 --> 00:31:40,653
without you.

328
00:31:41,529 --> 00:31:43,239
No.

329
00:31:43,907 --> 00:31:45,033
Don't die.

330
00:31:48,119 --> 00:31:51,623
Please don't die, Hae-in. I'm sorry…

331
00:32:05,887 --> 00:32:07,305
My dear Hae-in…

332
00:32:17,065 --> 00:32:19,609
I'm sorry…

333
00:32:35,667 --> 00:32:39,671
Lady Luck is only on her side
since that evil bitch is so hardworking.

334
00:32:39,754 --> 00:32:41,798
She sure is something.

335
00:32:53,309 --> 00:32:54,394
Chairman Hong.

336
00:32:54,477 --> 00:32:56,396
Do you recognize where we are?

337
00:33:01,985 --> 00:33:05,071
Come on, don't be scared. We're home.

338
00:33:06,906 --> 00:33:08,199
Let's go inside.

339
00:33:15,873 --> 00:33:19,836
Ma'am, there are many
nice electric wheelchairs these days.

340
00:33:47,530 --> 00:33:51,367
The chairman may be out of it,
but he refuses to be fed

341
00:33:51,451 --> 00:33:52,577
by anyone but me.

342
00:33:52,660 --> 00:33:56,039
So I can't leave his side.
That's why I asked you to come here.

343
00:33:56,122 --> 00:33:59,751
We understand. It's only thanks to you
that he woke up.

344
00:33:59,834 --> 00:34:02,128
Enough with the flattery.
Explain yourselves.

345
00:34:02,211 --> 00:34:04,714
How could he hold
such a press conference right now?

346
00:34:04,797 --> 00:34:07,508
We had no idea either.
Chairman Yoon suddenly--

347
00:34:07,592 --> 00:34:09,010
You should've known better.

348
00:34:09,093 --> 00:34:11,137
You're only getting paid so much

349
00:34:11,220 --> 00:34:13,806
so you'd prevent
such disasters from occurring.

350
00:34:14,307 --> 00:34:16,350
Goodness, should I not have said that?

351
00:34:16,434 --> 00:34:18,686
"You have no right
to say such things to us."

352
00:34:18,770 --> 00:34:21,481
"What do you know when you only cook
and nurse the chairman?"

353
00:34:21,564 --> 00:34:24,442
-Is that it?
-Of course not, ma'am.

354
00:34:24,525 --> 00:34:27,570
In that case, submit all the drafts to me
before you give them

355
00:34:27,653 --> 00:34:31,115
to Chairman Yoon and tell the PR Team
to come by tomorrow morning.

356
00:34:31,199 --> 00:34:32,742
What for?

357
00:34:32,825 --> 00:34:35,078
Do you not read the news?
The public is enraged.

358
00:34:35,161 --> 00:34:38,790
They're sympathizing with
the former management and criticizing us.

359
00:34:38,873 --> 00:34:41,501
Am I the only one who's worried
about the falling stock prices?

360
00:34:41,584 --> 00:34:43,461
The anchor LPs are furious.

361
00:34:43,544 --> 00:34:44,712
They're worried that

362
00:34:44,796 --> 00:34:47,423
the exit point will be delayed
due to the plummeting stocks.

363
00:34:47,507 --> 00:34:50,259
Rumor has it they want
to set up a co-GP investor.

364
00:34:51,010 --> 00:34:54,514
We must find the secret fund
if we want them to shut up.

365
00:34:54,597 --> 00:34:55,723
Did you dig into it?

366
00:34:55,807 --> 00:34:58,226
Yes, it was confirmed that Jamal Ibrahim,

367
00:34:58,309 --> 00:35:01,938
the bank president of LCC Investment Bank
in Labuan, Malaysia,

368
00:35:02,021 --> 00:35:03,648
managed the account.

369
00:35:03,731 --> 00:35:06,317
I think he withdrew the money
and wired it.

370
00:35:06,400 --> 00:35:07,860
-How much?
-Almost 900 billion won.

371
00:35:09,612 --> 00:35:11,197
Send someone to Labuan right now.

372
00:35:11,864 --> 00:35:13,950
Find out the next route.

373
00:35:14,826 --> 00:35:17,829
This restaurant is known
for their kal-guksu.

374
00:35:18,830 --> 00:35:20,873
-Try to eat.
-I'm sorry.

375
00:35:21,874 --> 00:35:23,167
I don't think I can.

376
00:35:24,836 --> 00:35:27,672
You need to eat well at times like this.

377
00:35:28,631 --> 00:35:30,007
Your family relies on you.

378
00:35:30,091 --> 00:35:34,095
You need to stay strong
if you want your kids to do the same.

379
00:35:34,178 --> 00:35:36,389
They don't look up to me for strength.

380
00:35:37,473 --> 00:35:39,308
I'm not the pillar of our family.

381
00:35:39,392 --> 00:35:42,937
In fact, it was my father all along.

382
00:35:43,020 --> 00:35:46,190
That hurt me at times,
but I was honestly relieved too.

383
00:35:48,442 --> 00:35:49,443
Pathetic, right?

384
00:35:50,069 --> 00:35:52,655
I was relieved
that my kids didn't rely on me.

385
00:35:52,738 --> 00:35:55,199
My daughter is dying,

386
00:35:57,660 --> 00:36:00,246
and I told her to trust me.

387
00:36:01,038 --> 00:36:04,500
But I doubt that meant anything to her.

388
00:36:04,584 --> 00:36:06,210
You're wrong.

389
00:36:06,294 --> 00:36:08,296
Our kids don't look at us that way.

390
00:36:08,379 --> 00:36:10,631
My father passed away before his time.

391
00:36:10,715 --> 00:36:11,966
But even to this day,

392
00:36:12,049 --> 00:36:14,302
I think of him
when I need to make a tough decision.

393
00:36:14,385 --> 00:36:16,179
"What would he have done?"

394
00:36:16,721 --> 00:36:18,097
You are

395
00:36:19,557 --> 00:36:21,100
a lighthouse to your kids

396
00:36:22,143 --> 00:36:24,061
no matter who you are.

397
00:36:24,145 --> 00:36:26,355
So eat well, stay strong,

398
00:36:26,439 --> 00:36:29,525
hold your head up, and shine your light.

399
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:32,486
Here.

400
00:36:33,362 --> 00:36:34,197
Here.

401
00:36:35,656 --> 00:36:36,657
Let's eat.

402
00:36:37,200 --> 00:36:39,076
Even the tastiest kal-guksu is bad

403
00:36:39,660 --> 00:36:40,578
if it gets soggy.

404
00:36:55,593 --> 00:36:57,595
"What did I just watch? Is this a drama?"

405
00:36:57,678 --> 00:37:00,264
"She's still foolishly in love
with her ex-husband."

406
00:37:00,348 --> 00:37:02,058
"I've never seen someone terminally ill

407
00:37:02,141 --> 00:37:03,351
-so in love."
-Enough.

408
00:37:05,394 --> 00:37:08,189
You've become the talk of the town
while you've been asleep.

409
00:37:08,272 --> 00:37:09,774
Don't be silly. It's mortifying.

410
00:37:09,857 --> 00:37:12,985
What do you mean?
You're going through dramatic changes.

411
00:37:13,069 --> 00:37:15,363
You were ambitious
about joining the One Trillion Club.

412
00:37:15,446 --> 00:37:17,740
Then your family went broke
and fled in a single day.

413
00:37:17,823 --> 00:37:19,784
And now, you're Juliet.

414
00:37:20,743 --> 00:37:23,454
Simply put,
people think I'm hopelessly in love

415
00:37:23,537 --> 00:37:26,624
with my ex-husband and that I revealed
my illness just to save him.

416
00:37:27,583 --> 00:37:29,293
-That's true.
-That's why I'm mortified.

417
00:37:30,878 --> 00:37:33,005
There are other things to worry about.

418
00:37:33,631 --> 00:37:34,632
Such as?

419
00:37:39,220 --> 00:37:40,388
What's this?

420
00:37:42,306 --> 00:37:43,516
I bought a formal dress.

421
00:37:43,599 --> 00:37:45,643
I bought it at full price
at a department store.

422
00:37:46,310 --> 00:37:48,521
-What does this signify?
-You tell me.

423
00:37:48,604 --> 00:37:50,398
That I'm very excited

424
00:37:51,023 --> 00:37:52,483
about your return.

425
00:37:53,609 --> 00:37:55,361
But I should get a refund.

426
00:37:55,444 --> 00:37:56,279
Don't bother.

427
00:37:56,904 --> 00:37:58,406
They'll assign you to someone else.

428
00:37:59,073 --> 00:38:00,074
You can wear it then.

429
00:38:00,741 --> 00:38:02,410
-No thanks.
-Why not?

430
00:38:02,493 --> 00:38:04,120
You know I'm shy around strangers.

431
00:38:04,203 --> 00:38:07,123
Given my occupation,
I won't have many opportunities.

432
00:38:08,124 --> 00:38:10,710
So come back. I'll be waiting.

433
00:38:11,502 --> 00:38:12,753
I can't guarantee that.

434
00:38:13,838 --> 00:38:15,589
But I'll do my best.

435
00:38:15,673 --> 00:38:18,676
I thought that didn't matter.
You always said to just make it work.

436
00:38:19,677 --> 00:38:21,012
So I'll say the same.

437
00:38:22,054 --> 00:38:23,973
Come back before I pay
all the installments.

438
00:38:26,434 --> 00:38:28,144
And when is that?

439
00:38:28,227 --> 00:38:29,103
In six months.

440
00:38:30,688 --> 00:38:32,440
-That's a bit--
-Just come back.

441
00:38:33,941 --> 00:38:35,735
Fine, I will.

442
00:38:36,402 --> 00:38:37,361
Why are you mad?

443
00:38:41,324 --> 00:38:42,325
I'll…

444
00:38:43,659 --> 00:38:44,744
give you a hug today

445
00:38:45,411 --> 00:38:46,829
because you finally woke up.

446
00:39:03,054 --> 00:39:04,347
Look at this.

447
00:39:04,430 --> 00:39:08,976
I became a divorcée who's still in love
with her ex in a single day.

448
00:39:13,814 --> 00:39:14,940
Is this funny to you?

449
00:39:15,024 --> 00:39:17,568
Why would you let that bother you?

450
00:39:19,570 --> 00:39:20,571
Look behind you.

451
00:39:27,828 --> 00:39:29,705
They were pitying me, weren't they?

452
00:39:31,582 --> 00:39:33,376
No one has ever looked at me
that way before.

453
00:39:33,459 --> 00:39:35,044
It's a first.

454
00:39:36,337 --> 00:39:38,047
This won't do.

455
00:39:39,006 --> 00:39:40,800
Dote on me in front of them.

456
00:39:42,343 --> 00:39:43,427
"In front of them"?

457
00:39:44,053 --> 00:39:46,639
-How?
-First…

458
00:39:46,722 --> 00:39:49,433
-Gaze at me lovingly.
-"Lovingly"?

459
00:39:58,401 --> 00:39:59,235
Like this?

460
00:40:08,869 --> 00:40:11,163
Well…

461
00:40:18,879 --> 00:40:19,880
Not bad.

462
00:40:32,685 --> 00:40:34,186
How long will you keep looking?

463
00:40:34,937 --> 00:40:35,938
What?

464
00:40:36,439 --> 00:40:37,565
What's your left arm doing?

465
00:40:39,358 --> 00:40:40,359
Right.

466
00:40:41,277 --> 00:40:42,153
Like this?

467
00:40:53,122 --> 00:40:56,292
SUNGMIN UNIVERSITY MEDICAL CENTER

468
00:41:14,685 --> 00:41:16,312
I was surprised you called.

469
00:41:16,395 --> 00:41:17,605
I had something to say.

470
00:41:18,063 --> 00:41:19,023
How are you feeling?

471
00:41:19,607 --> 00:41:20,733
I'm doing better.

472
00:41:20,816 --> 00:41:22,318
I'm leaving tomorrow.

473
00:41:23,652 --> 00:41:24,695
Why so soon?

474
00:41:24,778 --> 00:41:28,073
-There's not much they can do for me.
-Then come back home.

475
00:41:28,157 --> 00:41:29,366
It'd be more convenient.

476
00:41:29,450 --> 00:41:31,452
I didn't call to discuss that.

477
00:41:32,495 --> 00:41:34,246
-I'm listening.
-I know you're in a pickle.

478
00:41:34,330 --> 00:41:38,209
You're struggling to deal with the media.
The anchor LPs must be burdening you.

479
00:41:38,292 --> 00:41:40,461
You wouldn't have
enough stocks to stop them

480
00:41:40,544 --> 00:41:43,380
even if they wanted a new GP.

481
00:41:45,049 --> 00:41:46,050
So you know.

482
00:41:46,675 --> 00:41:47,843
It's all thanks to you.

483
00:41:47,927 --> 00:41:49,053
So…

484
00:41:51,013 --> 00:41:52,348
are you worried about me?

485
00:41:52,431 --> 00:41:55,726
No. I don't feel bad about your situation.

486
00:41:56,352 --> 00:42:00,022
Provoke me again,
and you'll lose something even bigger.

487
00:42:01,440 --> 00:42:02,525
That's all.

488
00:42:06,695 --> 00:42:08,030
Fine.

489
00:42:08,113 --> 00:42:09,740
That may be why you called.

490
00:42:11,367 --> 00:42:12,826
But my heart skipped a beat

491
00:42:14,745 --> 00:42:17,623
when I got your call
even though I knew why you called.

492
00:42:19,333 --> 00:42:20,501
You don't know

493
00:42:21,919 --> 00:42:24,129
how long I've had these feelings

494
00:42:24,213 --> 00:42:25,839
or when they first developed.

495
00:42:26,507 --> 00:42:27,341
No, I don't.

496
00:42:32,179 --> 00:42:33,180
And I don't need to.

497
00:42:34,807 --> 00:42:35,891
Do you remember why

498
00:42:36,725 --> 00:42:38,894
I cut ties with you in university?

499
00:42:38,978 --> 00:42:41,438
I was grateful for your help
when I was struggling.

500
00:42:41,522 --> 00:42:43,983
But you were the reason
why I was struggling

501
00:42:44,900 --> 00:42:46,068
in the first place.

502
00:42:47,027 --> 00:42:49,989
Maybe you should've liked me back
before I did those things.

503
00:42:51,073 --> 00:42:52,491
I only did such things

504
00:42:52,575 --> 00:42:55,619
because I couldn't get close to you
no matter how hard I tried.

505
00:42:55,703 --> 00:42:57,329
That's how you treat others.

506
00:42:58,205 --> 00:42:59,415
Look at you even now.

507
00:42:59,957 --> 00:43:03,127
You pushed me into a ditch
so you could get me out of it.

508
00:43:04,545 --> 00:43:06,422
So who could possibly like you?

509
00:43:07,172 --> 00:43:08,966
Then what about Hyun-woo?

510
00:43:10,551 --> 00:43:11,927
Does he deserve your love?

511
00:43:12,845 --> 00:43:15,180
He was going to leave you.

512
00:43:15,264 --> 00:43:18,142
Did your tumor mess with your memory?
Did you forget?

513
00:43:18,225 --> 00:43:19,393
He's with me now.

514
00:43:23,188 --> 00:43:24,356
He's with me

515
00:43:25,274 --> 00:43:26,108
right now.

516
00:43:29,320 --> 00:43:30,571
Must I explain more?

517
00:43:47,796 --> 00:43:50,007
-Are you done talking?
-Mr. Baek.

518
00:43:50,799 --> 00:43:52,676
Why are you still by her side?

519
00:43:52,760 --> 00:43:54,845
Why must I tell you?

520
00:43:54,928 --> 00:43:57,973
Did you develop feelings
after finding out she was dying?

521
00:43:58,057 --> 00:44:00,392
Or are you hoping
she'll leave you something?

522
00:44:03,395 --> 00:44:04,480
Just come to me.

523
00:44:04,563 --> 00:44:07,066
I'll give you anything you want
if you leave her side.

524
00:44:17,534 --> 00:44:20,079
You're really testing my patience,
so just go.

525
00:44:26,669 --> 00:44:27,503
Hey.

526
00:44:33,092 --> 00:44:36,261
I didn't want to tell you something
I haven't even told her yet.

527
00:44:36,345 --> 00:44:38,931
But try all you want.
I'm not going anywhere.

528
00:44:39,014 --> 00:44:41,517
I'm going to stay by her side forever.

529
00:44:42,101 --> 00:44:42,976
I'll be with her.

530
00:44:43,936 --> 00:44:46,230
So don't hold your breath
and just get lost.

531
00:45:02,913 --> 00:45:04,039
You're home.

532
00:45:05,499 --> 00:45:06,834
The chairman is here.

533
00:45:06,917 --> 00:45:07,835
Did you hear?

534
00:45:11,922 --> 00:45:12,881
You look happy.

535
00:45:13,716 --> 00:45:14,717
Of course not.

536
00:45:14,800 --> 00:45:18,554
How can I when
the love of your life broke your heart?

537
00:45:19,722 --> 00:45:21,098
What happened to your face?

538
00:45:21,181 --> 00:45:22,933
-Are you hurt?
-It's none…

539
00:45:24,601 --> 00:45:25,978
of your business.

540
00:45:27,354 --> 00:45:29,648
I've always lived a hopeless life.

541
00:45:30,524 --> 00:45:32,234
No pain is greater than another,

542
00:45:32,776 --> 00:45:34,611
and I don't care if I get hurt.

543
00:45:35,571 --> 00:45:37,030
So quit trying to act

544
00:45:37,614 --> 00:45:38,615
like a typical mom.

545
00:45:41,660 --> 00:45:42,661
You have a guest.

546
00:45:53,922 --> 00:45:56,091
Why haven't you been picking up?

547
00:45:56,175 --> 00:46:00,053
Do you feel no guilt
about what happened to me?

548
00:46:02,639 --> 00:46:05,017
I told you not to call me,
so why are you here?

549
00:46:06,518 --> 00:46:10,564
I dodged getting arrested,
but they haven't let me off the hook.

550
00:46:10,647 --> 00:46:14,151
-Baek Hyun-woo won't sit still!
-So?

551
00:46:14,234 --> 00:46:17,070
Will I be the only one going down
if the world finds out

552
00:46:17,154 --> 00:46:19,406
about the double contract
and the land investment fraud?

553
00:46:19,490 --> 00:46:22,785
Do you think you'll keep your position,
Chairman Yoon?

554
00:46:23,952 --> 00:46:27,039
This is the amount of stocks
Eun-sung's LPs have.

555
00:46:27,122 --> 00:46:28,499
I sounded him out today.

556
00:46:28,582 --> 00:46:30,292
"Aren't your LPs furious?"

557
00:46:30,375 --> 00:46:31,960
"Don't they want a new GP?"

558
00:46:32,044 --> 00:46:33,545
And he agreed.

559
00:46:34,129 --> 00:46:35,172
That means--

560
00:46:35,255 --> 00:46:38,091
He still hasn't located
Chairman Hong's secret fund.

561
00:46:38,175 --> 00:46:39,510
Were you aware

562
00:46:40,093 --> 00:46:41,845
of the secret fund in Switzerland?

563
00:46:41,929 --> 00:46:44,264
Three corporations
are founded in the Virgin Islands,

564
00:46:44,348 --> 00:46:45,849
Moldova, and Singapore.

565
00:46:45,933 --> 00:46:49,102
The secret fund in Switzerland
is moved to Singapore.

566
00:46:49,186 --> 00:46:50,813
Then the Virgin Islands

567
00:46:50,896 --> 00:46:54,024
make it look like
they lent money to Moldova,

568
00:46:54,107 --> 00:46:57,069
and Singapore underwrites Moldova's debt.

569
00:46:58,195 --> 00:47:00,614
Then Moldova announces
that they can't pay it back?

570
00:47:00,697 --> 00:47:01,532
Correct.

571
00:47:02,157 --> 00:47:04,952
Then the Virgin Islands
files a default suit,

572
00:47:05,035 --> 00:47:06,912
and the court demands Singapore
to pay it back.

573
00:47:08,497 --> 00:47:11,458
The court makes it possible
to move the secret fund legally.

574
00:47:11,542 --> 00:47:13,877
Once everything is done,
these three corporations

575
00:47:13,961 --> 00:47:16,588
shut down
and make it difficult to track the fund.

576
00:47:16,672 --> 00:47:18,549
They continue to launder this way.

577
00:47:18,632 --> 00:47:22,469
And finally, they send the money
to a bank in Labuan, Malaysia.

578
00:47:24,054 --> 00:47:25,055
Incredible.

579
00:47:25,138 --> 00:47:28,851
Does that mean the secret fund
is in Malaysia right now?

580
00:47:28,934 --> 00:47:32,312
I don't think so because Eun-sung
sent someone to Labuan today.

581
00:47:32,396 --> 00:47:35,274
So he doesn't know
the final destination either.

582
00:47:38,986 --> 00:47:40,404
By the way,

583
00:47:41,280 --> 00:47:42,823
how did you know this?

584
00:47:44,366 --> 00:47:47,494
Many people are unhappy
about the current situation

585
00:47:47,578 --> 00:47:49,288
but they can't express it.

586
00:47:49,371 --> 00:47:53,166
Some of them have been working
for Queens for over 30 years.

587
00:47:53,917 --> 00:47:56,753
Secretary Jang had been
Chairman Hong's secretary for years.

588
00:47:56,837 --> 00:47:59,548
But he turned down a hefty salary
and resigned.

589
00:48:02,134 --> 00:48:03,176
Secretary Jang.

590
00:48:04,303 --> 00:48:05,721
How have you been?

591
00:48:05,804 --> 00:48:08,849
They told you these things for us?

592
00:48:08,932 --> 00:48:12,561
No, for the company they dedicated
their entire lives to.

593
00:48:13,312 --> 00:48:15,856
They don't want to see
the company crumble anymore.

594
00:48:17,941 --> 00:48:19,151
What about you?

595
00:48:20,736 --> 00:48:22,905
Why are you doing this? For the company?

596
00:48:22,988 --> 00:48:24,740
Yes, it's for the company.

597
00:48:27,743 --> 00:48:30,996
Because I know how much you love

598
00:48:31,580 --> 00:48:32,414
your company.

599
00:48:44,092 --> 00:48:47,095
We have taken into consideration
each of our members' opinions.

600
00:48:47,179 --> 00:48:49,514
You have violated
your duty of confidentiality

601
00:48:49,598 --> 00:48:51,224
and leaked information--

602
00:48:56,521 --> 00:48:58,357
-Who are you?
-Right.

603
00:48:58,440 --> 00:49:01,401
We're here to defend our client,
Mr. Baek Hyun-woo.

604
00:49:01,485 --> 00:49:04,696
Look. You have no right
to interfere in this internal audit.

605
00:49:04,780 --> 00:49:08,283
According to Article 12, Paragraph 1,
Item 3 and Article 11, Paragraph 4

606
00:49:08,367 --> 00:49:11,495
of the Administrative Procedure Act,
our client has the right to hire

607
00:49:11,578 --> 00:49:12,996
an attorney to represent him.

608
00:49:16,917 --> 00:49:17,960
Let's continue.

609
00:49:18,043 --> 00:49:20,629
Due to these reasons,
we've decided to fire you--

610
00:49:20,712 --> 00:49:21,755
Your reason for firing him

611
00:49:21,838 --> 00:49:24,716
is that you received a tip-off
from a rival company's executive

612
00:49:24,800 --> 00:49:27,260
who claimed that Mr. Baek leaked
VIP information to them.

613
00:49:27,344 --> 00:49:30,555
And you confirmed that he got his hands
on it by using his company ID.

614
00:49:30,639 --> 00:49:32,766
-Yes, and?
-When did you receive that tip-off?

615
00:49:33,266 --> 00:49:34,142
On August 6th.

616
00:49:34,226 --> 00:49:35,978
When did Mr. Baek extract the VIP list?

617
00:49:36,061 --> 00:49:37,145
August 1st and 2nd.

618
00:49:37,229 --> 00:49:38,689
-Two different occasions.
-How odd.

619
00:49:38,772 --> 00:49:42,192
His intranet ID was deleted on July 28th.

620
00:49:42,275 --> 00:49:43,276
Correct.

621
00:49:43,360 --> 00:49:46,071
I returned my ID card,
company card, laptop,

622
00:49:46,154 --> 00:49:47,781
and everything else that day.

623
00:49:47,864 --> 00:49:50,826
Maybe it wasn't your ID.
You could've used someone else's.

624
00:49:50,909 --> 00:49:51,952
Like whose?

625
00:49:52,035 --> 00:49:54,079
Maybe one of his team members'.

626
00:49:54,162 --> 00:49:59,334
That means a regular employee has access
to Queens Department Store's VIP list.

627
00:49:59,418 --> 00:50:00,836
-Isn't that a problem?
-Correct.

628
00:50:00,919 --> 00:50:04,006
There needs to be proof that
the certain information was restricted

629
00:50:04,089 --> 00:50:05,632
for it to be considered classified.

630
00:50:05,716 --> 00:50:08,760
If anyone could gain access
and download the material,

631
00:50:08,844 --> 00:50:11,013
that just shows that the store

632
00:50:11,096 --> 00:50:13,598
didn't keep the VIP list a secret.

633
00:50:13,682 --> 00:50:18,145
The real problem is the embezzlement,
and he signed all the related documents.

634
00:50:18,228 --> 00:50:21,231
We requested an authentication
to a document examiner who used to be

635
00:50:21,314 --> 00:50:25,068
the former Chief of Document at the NFS
regarding those 27 signatures.

636
00:50:25,152 --> 00:50:27,362
The sizes and the details
of the signatures

637
00:50:27,446 --> 00:50:29,948
were proven to be exactly the same.

638
00:50:30,032 --> 00:50:32,951
This is only possible
if his signature was duplicated.

639
00:50:33,744 --> 00:50:38,040
We can't trust this result
since you requested it.

640
00:50:38,123 --> 00:50:40,375
Then let's ask the prosecution
to appraise it.

641
00:50:40,459 --> 00:50:42,961
For your information,
there's no fine for document forgery.

642
00:50:43,045 --> 00:50:45,589
Only imprisonment
for a maximum of three years.

643
00:50:49,092 --> 00:50:50,218
We hope

644
00:50:50,302 --> 00:50:52,721
you'll make

645
00:50:53,680 --> 00:50:54,890
a wise decision.

646
00:51:54,449 --> 00:51:55,867
-It's me.
-Hello, sir.

647
00:51:58,954 --> 00:52:00,038
Get rid

648
00:52:00,956 --> 00:52:01,957
of Baek Hyun-woo.

649
00:52:03,542 --> 00:52:05,293
He's a nuisance to both of us.

650
00:52:05,377 --> 00:52:06,628
Boracay, was it?

651
00:52:07,462 --> 00:52:08,421
I'll send you there

652
00:52:08,505 --> 00:52:10,215
and pay you handsomely.

653
00:52:10,298 --> 00:52:11,174
Chairman Yoon.

654
00:52:11,258 --> 00:52:14,469
There was a hiccup last time
because I was a bit careless.

655
00:52:14,553 --> 00:52:16,930
I'll take care of it properly this time.

656
00:52:30,360 --> 00:52:33,446
The more attorneys, the better.
It's great that you have us.

657
00:52:33,530 --> 00:52:38,493
Despite having different specialties,
we got together to help a friend.

658
00:52:39,161 --> 00:52:40,579
We're like the Avengers.

659
00:52:40,662 --> 00:52:44,166
I'm sorry, but I'm also here
because people kept asking

660
00:52:44,249 --> 00:52:46,793
if you were
getting back together with your ex.

661
00:52:46,877 --> 00:52:47,836
Are you?

662
00:52:54,843 --> 00:52:56,261
That's none of your business.

663
00:52:56,344 --> 00:52:58,305
You majored in commercial law.

664
00:52:58,388 --> 00:53:02,559
He's right. You excelled at
the Bills of Exchange Act and Check Act.

665
00:53:02,642 --> 00:53:04,978
That's the past.
I take all sorts of cases now.

666
00:53:05,061 --> 00:53:07,397
Take a look at this

667
00:53:07,480 --> 00:53:08,982
and track the money.

668
00:53:09,482 --> 00:53:10,609
WSB SWITZERLAND BANK

669
00:53:12,027 --> 00:53:13,778
Where did you get these?

670
00:53:18,450 --> 00:53:19,284
Hello.

671
00:53:20,243 --> 00:53:21,494
Take this.

672
00:53:21,578 --> 00:53:23,830
-I'll throw this away on my way out.
-Thank you.

673
00:53:23,914 --> 00:53:25,081
-Second basement level?
-Yes.

674
00:53:25,165 --> 00:53:26,917
Secretary Na, hello.

675
00:53:27,000 --> 00:53:27,834
Hello.

676
00:53:29,920 --> 00:53:30,921
Have one.

677
00:53:31,421 --> 00:53:32,255
Thank you.

678
00:53:55,070 --> 00:53:57,030
Eun-sung is looking
for the chairman's secret fund

679
00:53:57,113 --> 00:53:58,990
so he can buy more stocks.

680
00:53:59,074 --> 00:54:00,700
A secret fund? How much?

681
00:54:00,784 --> 00:54:01,910
Nine hundred billion.

682
00:54:07,582 --> 00:54:08,416
I'm going

683
00:54:10,043 --> 00:54:11,253
to find it first.

684
00:54:12,295 --> 00:54:14,589
Ma'am, be careful of the UV rays.

685
00:54:15,215 --> 00:54:16,424
Why do you keep coming?

686
00:54:16,508 --> 00:54:18,426
Didn't you side with Beom-ja?

687
00:54:18,510 --> 00:54:19,427
Sorry?

688
00:54:19,511 --> 00:54:21,596
Gosh, you got the wrong idea.

689
00:54:21,680 --> 00:54:23,139
That time,

690
00:54:23,223 --> 00:54:25,267
I felt terrible because she begged me

691
00:54:25,350 --> 00:54:28,353
to help her see her father just once.

692
00:54:28,436 --> 00:54:29,980
I'm unusually soft at times.

693
00:54:30,063 --> 00:54:31,773
Fine. Side with whomever you pity.

694
00:54:31,856 --> 00:54:34,359
Gosh, Ms. Moh!

695
00:54:34,442 --> 00:54:35,902
You know me.

696
00:54:35,986 --> 00:54:38,947
I only side with money and power.

697
00:54:39,030 --> 00:54:42,409
After all, you're the queen right now.

698
00:54:43,535 --> 00:54:46,955
I don't need to be the CEO
or anything like that.

699
00:54:47,038 --> 00:54:48,957
I'm just going to stick with you

700
00:54:49,666 --> 00:54:50,917
like your maid.

701
00:54:51,001 --> 00:54:52,669
Maid, my foot.

702
00:54:53,920 --> 00:54:54,838
Let's see then.

703
00:54:54,921 --> 00:54:56,172
Sure thing.

704
00:54:56,256 --> 00:55:00,593
I, the amazing Grace,
will serve you amazingly.

705
00:55:07,559 --> 00:55:09,686
Sir, do you remember this room?

706
00:55:09,769 --> 00:55:11,855
They said being in a familiar environment

707
00:55:11,938 --> 00:55:13,857
would help you recover,
so I brought you here.

708
00:55:13,940 --> 00:55:15,942
It's not easy to be a caregiver.

709
00:55:16,026 --> 00:55:18,236
Let me give you a massage later.

710
00:55:18,320 --> 00:55:20,155
How about some frankincense oil?

711
00:55:20,238 --> 00:55:21,072
Sure.

712
00:55:45,138 --> 00:55:46,139
Thank you.

713
00:55:46,723 --> 00:55:49,100
You can go and let him rest.

714
00:56:04,657 --> 00:56:05,492
So?

715
00:56:06,159 --> 00:56:07,660
Does that bring back memories?

716
00:56:07,744 --> 00:56:09,454
Tell me. Where's my money?

717
00:56:09,537 --> 00:56:12,665
Where's the secret fund that
you stashed away under my name?

718
00:56:40,276 --> 00:56:42,278
Keep watching her no matter what.

719
00:56:43,154 --> 00:56:45,198
Who knows what else she'll do to him?

720
00:56:49,994 --> 00:56:50,829
I'm hanging up.

721
00:57:12,350 --> 00:57:13,268
Goodness.

722
00:57:13,351 --> 00:57:15,854
Gosh, he's showing so much skin
in broad daylight.

723
00:57:31,995 --> 00:57:32,829
What is it?

724
00:57:33,496 --> 00:57:34,456
"Check me out."

725
00:57:35,331 --> 00:57:36,583
"I'm good-looking."

726
00:57:37,208 --> 00:57:38,835
"I have a great body too."

727
00:57:38,918 --> 00:57:39,752
Is that it?

728
00:57:41,045 --> 00:57:42,046
Goodness.

729
00:58:08,448 --> 00:58:09,407
What are you doing?

730
00:58:11,284 --> 00:58:12,118
I…

731
00:58:12,702 --> 00:58:13,536
Well…

732
00:58:15,538 --> 00:58:17,916
I believe you were peeping.

733
00:58:17,999 --> 00:58:20,710
No, I wasn't. I was just passing by

734
00:58:20,793 --> 00:58:22,587
when I saw you there.

735
00:58:27,133 --> 00:58:28,009
Do you want some?

736
00:58:30,303 --> 00:58:31,763
-What is that?
-Mulberries.

737
00:58:31,846 --> 00:58:33,139
As in…

738
00:58:35,433 --> 00:58:37,268
-berries?
-Yes, you're right.

739
00:58:37,352 --> 00:58:39,103
They're good for women.

740
00:58:42,857 --> 00:58:44,567
-How much?
-They're not for sale.

741
00:58:44,651 --> 00:58:45,652
They're free.

742
00:58:45,735 --> 00:58:46,694
Why would you…

743
00:58:49,697 --> 00:58:51,658
How original. I'll give you that.

744
00:58:52,534 --> 00:58:53,493
What?

745
00:58:54,202 --> 00:58:57,580
You're the first guy
to make a move using mulberries.

746
00:58:58,248 --> 00:59:00,250
But let me be clear.

747
00:59:00,333 --> 00:59:01,417
Accepting these

748
00:59:01,501 --> 00:59:03,461
doesn't mean I'm accepting your love.

749
00:59:06,714 --> 00:59:09,259
-What's your MBTI?
-What?

750
00:59:09,968 --> 00:59:12,387
I think you're an ISTJ.

751
00:59:12,470 --> 00:59:14,847
-I… What?
-You don't express emotions well.

752
00:59:14,931 --> 00:59:19,269
You're a perfectionist with a good memory.
You look cold, but you're actually soft.

753
00:59:19,352 --> 00:59:22,564
Both Robert De Niro
and Natalie Portman are this type.

754
00:59:25,942 --> 00:59:27,068
What is he saying?

755
00:59:28,987 --> 00:59:30,572
But why are you home?

756
00:59:30,655 --> 00:59:32,615
Shouldn't you be working like the others?

757
00:59:32,699 --> 00:59:33,700
I don't work

758
00:59:35,034 --> 00:59:35,868
that much.

759
00:59:36,494 --> 00:59:37,453
Why not?

760
00:59:37,537 --> 00:59:39,414
Because life is too short.

761
00:59:40,206 --> 00:59:42,375
I just work enough to be self-sufficient.

762
00:59:50,800 --> 00:59:52,760
So what? He's a self-sufficient farmer?

763
01:00:03,688 --> 01:00:05,565
Did he save these for me?

764
01:00:05,648 --> 01:00:06,649
Jeez.

765
01:00:08,985 --> 01:00:10,570
Natalie Portman?

766
01:00:30,840 --> 01:00:32,050
Goodness!

767
01:00:32,759 --> 01:00:34,677
That's a lot!

768
01:00:34,761 --> 01:00:37,138
They're from Yeong-song.

769
01:00:37,221 --> 01:00:38,931
He picked some mulberries.

770
01:00:39,015 --> 01:00:40,391
He says he has more.

771
01:00:40,475 --> 01:00:42,060
He picked way too many,

772
01:00:42,143 --> 01:00:43,936
so he's been sharing them.

773
01:00:45,855 --> 01:00:46,939
He's ridiculous.

774
01:00:47,023 --> 01:00:48,650
He could just sell the extra.

775
01:00:48,733 --> 01:00:51,319
He always puts aside
just enough for his family

776
01:00:51,402 --> 01:00:53,279
and gives away the rest.

777
01:00:53,363 --> 01:00:55,657
What'll we do with all this?

778
01:01:26,354 --> 01:01:29,774
Someone once told me that
the wise eat meat when times are rough.

779
01:01:29,857 --> 01:01:32,819
Yes, you're right.

780
01:01:32,902 --> 01:01:36,906
Determination alone
can't strengthen your willpower.

781
01:01:36,989 --> 01:01:38,950
Your health matters too.

782
01:01:39,033 --> 01:01:40,618
-Wipe your hands.
-Okay.

783
01:01:41,327 --> 01:01:45,415
Also, think about what you ate
on all your special occasions.

784
01:01:45,498 --> 01:01:46,874
It was meat.

785
01:01:46,958 --> 01:01:49,669
Right? Birthdays, graduations,
the day you got a new job…

786
01:01:49,752 --> 01:01:50,586
And look.

787
01:01:50,670 --> 01:01:54,006
We're celebrating her discharge
over some meat too.

788
01:01:54,090 --> 01:01:56,759
We always had Chinese food on my birthday.

789
01:01:56,843 --> 01:01:59,262
What's sweet and sour pork?
What about chili chicken?

790
01:02:01,389 --> 01:02:02,724
-Let me grill it.
-You?

791
01:02:03,558 --> 01:02:05,727
You only eat meat

792
01:02:05,810 --> 01:02:07,311
that's served on your plate.

793
01:02:07,395 --> 01:02:10,022
I'll be grilling
my family's meat from now on.

794
01:02:10,106 --> 01:02:11,399
Put down your tongs.

795
01:02:11,983 --> 01:02:13,151
-Let me.
-Yes, sir.

796
01:02:20,491 --> 01:02:21,617
Hae-in, I remember

797
01:02:21,701 --> 01:02:24,662
the doctor saying
that your WBC mattered the most.

798
01:02:24,746 --> 01:02:26,706
He said you needed to reach

799
01:02:26,789 --> 01:02:29,417
a certain level
to receive treatment in Germany.

800
01:02:30,418 --> 01:02:31,419
That's correct.

801
01:02:31,502 --> 01:02:32,920
My WBC needs to be

802
01:02:33,004 --> 01:02:36,841
between 4,000
and 10,000 cells per microliter.

803
01:02:36,924 --> 01:02:38,968
How high was it in Germany?

804
01:02:39,051 --> 01:02:40,261
It was 1,500 cells/µL.

805
01:02:42,054 --> 01:02:42,972
That's so low.

806
01:02:43,055 --> 01:02:45,600
But it went up a lot recently.

807
01:02:45,683 --> 01:02:47,351
It's about 3,000 now.

808
01:02:48,603 --> 01:02:50,062
That's double the amount.

809
01:02:50,146 --> 01:02:51,773
I'm proud of you.

810
01:02:51,856 --> 01:02:54,025
Well… It's not that big of a deal.

811
01:02:54,108 --> 01:02:57,570
-I still have over 1,000 to go.
-You're almost there.

812
01:02:57,653 --> 01:02:59,363
Try harder.

813
01:02:59,447 --> 01:03:02,909
Hey, this isn't like studying.
I can't just "try harder."

814
01:03:02,992 --> 01:03:05,995
In that case,
what should you do? Get injections and?

815
01:03:06,078 --> 01:03:07,538
I looked into it.

816
01:03:07,622 --> 01:03:11,417
It's all about her stamina and immunity.

817
01:03:11,501 --> 01:03:14,712
She needs to eat well
and take a lot of vitamins and proteins.

818
01:03:14,796 --> 01:03:16,088
She needs good rest too.

819
01:03:16,172 --> 01:03:19,383
Then she needs to eat a lot of meat

820
01:03:19,467 --> 01:03:20,301
and beans.

821
01:03:20,384 --> 01:03:22,345
I'm going to plan her diet.

822
01:03:29,477 --> 01:03:30,728
-Beom-jun.
-Yes?

823
01:03:30,812 --> 01:03:31,813
Flip them over.

824
01:03:32,730 --> 01:03:34,148
Right.

825
01:03:36,108 --> 01:03:36,984
No.

826
01:03:37,068 --> 01:03:38,736
They're burned. What should I do?

827
01:03:38,820 --> 01:03:40,112
We can just cut them off.

828
01:03:41,030 --> 01:03:43,157
-Can you give me the scissors?
-No.

829
01:03:43,241 --> 01:03:44,116
I'll do it.

830
01:03:45,451 --> 01:03:47,703
So she needs meat and beans.

831
01:03:47,787 --> 01:03:48,830
What else?

832
01:03:48,913 --> 01:03:51,332
Bananas and nuts…

833
01:03:51,999 --> 01:03:54,460
-This is good.
-Gosh.

834
01:03:54,544 --> 01:03:56,128
This is tasty.

835
01:03:57,046 --> 01:03:58,047
It's really good.

836
01:03:58,840 --> 01:04:00,424
-Look.
-He's excited.

837
01:04:02,885 --> 01:04:04,095
Goodness.

838
01:04:05,972 --> 01:04:07,098
You need to flip this.

839
01:04:08,766 --> 01:04:09,851
Look at this.

840
01:04:11,686 --> 01:04:13,312
She needs a lot of protein.

841
01:04:13,396 --> 01:04:14,730
She does.

842
01:04:19,235 --> 01:04:20,653
Eat while you do it.

843
01:04:21,320 --> 01:04:23,447
Wipe it off for her.

844
01:04:34,000 --> 01:04:34,834
Come in.

845
01:04:40,298 --> 01:04:42,091
This isn't working again.

846
01:04:44,468 --> 01:04:45,720
Is it not?

847
01:04:50,308 --> 01:04:52,226
You just need to press this part.

848
01:04:52,310 --> 01:04:55,062
I'm not as good as you.

849
01:04:56,772 --> 01:04:58,190
Should I buy a new one?

850
01:04:58,858 --> 01:04:59,859
Why?

851
01:04:59,942 --> 01:05:01,193
Because you struggle to use it.

852
01:05:01,277 --> 01:05:03,821
Then you can do it for me.
Look how good you are.

853
01:05:07,366 --> 01:05:08,326
I think

854
01:05:08,868 --> 01:05:09,827
I'm getting better…

855
01:05:11,996 --> 01:05:13,414
the more I dry your hair.

856
01:05:16,834 --> 01:05:17,668
You're right.

857
01:05:17,752 --> 01:05:19,378
You did a good job on the curls.

858
01:05:22,340 --> 01:05:25,509
Now that you're better,
keep drying my hair for me.

859
01:05:25,593 --> 01:05:26,761
Sure. That's not a problem.

860
01:05:27,345 --> 01:05:28,179
What else?

861
01:05:28,262 --> 01:05:32,016
Tell me what else
you want me to do, and I'll do it.

862
01:05:34,101 --> 01:05:35,144
I'm happy

863
01:05:35,728 --> 01:05:38,898
as long as you dry my hair
with the broken hair dryer.

864
01:05:41,150 --> 01:05:42,735
So just this?

865
01:05:42,818 --> 01:05:43,819
It's a big favor.

866
01:05:44,487 --> 01:05:46,697
You'd have to be by my side every day.

867
01:05:47,281 --> 01:05:48,616
I don't think

868
01:05:48,699 --> 01:05:51,035
I should be greedy for now.

869
01:05:53,329 --> 01:05:55,414
No, be greedy.

870
01:05:56,040 --> 01:05:56,916
You can.

871
01:05:56,999 --> 01:05:59,293
Don't try too hard to treat me well.

872
01:05:59,377 --> 01:06:03,089
I didn't confess my love to you
so that you'd treat me better.

873
01:06:03,172 --> 01:06:04,006
I was simply

874
01:06:05,216 --> 01:06:06,717
expressing my feelings.

875
01:06:06,801 --> 01:06:07,802
Same goes for me.

876
01:06:10,304 --> 01:06:11,222
My heart wants it.

877
01:06:13,224 --> 01:06:14,392
I want to do better

878
01:06:15,476 --> 01:06:16,769
if I can.

879
01:06:18,229 --> 01:06:19,271
That's how I feel.

880
01:06:26,404 --> 01:06:27,405
Yesterday…

881
01:06:28,155 --> 01:06:30,282
I couldn't recognize Soo-cheol's face

882
01:06:31,534 --> 01:06:33,953
for a few seconds.

883
01:06:35,079 --> 01:06:37,832
I couldn't remember
my doctor's name either.

884
01:06:38,791 --> 01:06:40,793
I also lost my way to my hospital room

885
01:06:41,335 --> 01:06:43,587
for a minute and just stood still.

886
01:06:45,798 --> 01:06:48,217
When my doctor
first told me about my illness,

887
01:06:48,843 --> 01:06:50,553
he mentioned memory loss,

888
01:06:50,636 --> 01:06:53,556
sensory loss, and speech impediment.

889
01:06:53,639 --> 01:06:55,182
But I didn't believe him.

890
01:06:56,642 --> 01:06:58,269
I thought that only happened to others.

891
01:06:59,228 --> 01:07:00,688
I thought I was different.

892
01:07:02,064 --> 01:07:05,901
But it's happening in that exact order.

893
01:07:06,527 --> 01:07:10,322
I can expect the next symptom,
and it's terrifying.

894
01:07:11,365 --> 01:07:12,908
I don't want you

895
01:07:12,992 --> 01:07:15,077
to be next to me when it happens.

896
01:07:19,707 --> 01:07:21,167
What are you saying?

897
01:07:21,250 --> 01:07:23,127
Let's be happy with where we are now.

898
01:07:25,087 --> 01:07:26,672
And when my illness worsens,

899
01:07:26,756 --> 01:07:28,174
I want you

900
01:07:29,383 --> 01:07:30,926
to leave me.

901
01:07:34,513 --> 01:07:35,556
That's my wish.

902
01:07:55,534 --> 01:07:57,244
What? When did he leave the game?

903
01:07:57,328 --> 01:07:58,412
Did something happen?

904
01:07:58,496 --> 01:07:59,413
DEACTIVATED MEMBER

905
01:08:00,206 --> 01:08:01,040
Damn it.

906
01:08:09,173 --> 01:08:10,007
Room service.

907
01:08:23,312 --> 01:08:24,146
Drink up.

908
01:08:32,696 --> 01:08:33,823
Is it that bitter?

909
01:08:38,285 --> 01:08:40,579
-Not as much as my life.
-Dear.

910
01:08:45,584 --> 01:08:47,378
Master, please talk casually to me.

911
01:08:47,461 --> 01:08:48,462
"Master"?

912
01:08:52,383 --> 01:08:54,635
Please teach me how to box.

913
01:08:54,718 --> 01:08:57,096
I couldn't land a single punch

914
01:08:57,179 --> 01:09:00,891
on Eun-sung last time
and fell down humiliatingly.

915
01:09:03,561 --> 01:09:04,854
I understand.

916
01:09:04,937 --> 01:09:07,273
But if you suddenly start working out
out of rage,

917
01:09:07,356 --> 01:09:09,525
-you'll injure your joints--
-Joints?

918
01:09:09,608 --> 01:09:10,651
That's fine by me!

919
01:09:10,734 --> 01:09:12,820
I'm going to go insane at this rate!

920
01:09:14,113 --> 01:09:17,992
What if I need to protect
my family in the future, but I can't?

921
01:09:20,077 --> 01:09:21,203
I'm dreading it.

922
01:09:21,287 --> 01:09:22,621
Oh, dear.

923
01:09:27,251 --> 01:09:28,419
Fine.

924
01:09:28,502 --> 01:09:29,587
I'll teach you.

925
01:09:31,213 --> 01:09:32,131
Thank you.

926
01:09:32,214 --> 01:09:33,382
Sit down.

927
01:09:33,465 --> 01:09:34,466
Sit down.

928
01:09:34,550 --> 01:09:35,634
Sit down.

929
01:09:37,887 --> 01:09:40,181
But since we're doing this in a haste,

930
01:09:40,264 --> 01:09:42,099
I can only teach you one thing.

931
01:09:42,183 --> 01:09:43,017
And what's that?

932
01:09:43,100 --> 01:09:44,518
Landing a single punch

933
01:09:46,061 --> 01:09:47,605
on someone powerful.

934
01:09:53,360 --> 01:09:55,237
There are two core skills.

935
01:09:56,322 --> 01:09:57,156
Soo-cheol.

936
01:09:58,699 --> 01:09:59,742
Hit me.

937
01:10:00,910 --> 01:10:01,744
Are you serious?

938
01:10:07,583 --> 01:10:08,792
Am I that strong?

939
01:10:10,461 --> 01:10:12,796
No, this is the first skill.

940
01:10:13,631 --> 01:10:14,506
Exaggerate.

941
01:10:14,590 --> 01:10:16,842
So that they'll feel arrogant and think,

942
01:10:16,926 --> 01:10:18,844
"He's no match for me."

943
01:10:18,928 --> 01:10:20,512
"I pretty much won."

944
01:10:20,596 --> 01:10:22,473
"I'm surprisingly strong."

945
01:10:23,265 --> 01:10:24,934
-I see.
-Okay, bring it on.

946
01:10:30,231 --> 01:10:31,982
-Well done.
-That really hurt!

947
01:10:32,066 --> 01:10:33,734
-I'm sorry.
-My nose!

948
01:10:33,817 --> 01:10:35,653
Why must I learn this?

949
01:10:36,195 --> 01:10:37,947
So they'll let down their guard.

950
01:10:38,030 --> 01:10:41,116
You must wait
until they let down their guard

951
01:10:41,200 --> 01:10:43,160
then land your critical punch.

952
01:10:43,244 --> 01:10:44,912
But get beaten up until then?

953
01:10:44,995 --> 01:10:46,747
That's the second skill.

954
01:10:46,830 --> 01:10:48,249
Endurance.

955
01:10:48,332 --> 01:10:50,542
You need stamina to take blows well.

956
01:10:51,126 --> 01:10:52,628
Do you think I can do that?

957
01:10:59,969 --> 01:11:02,179
Muhammad Ali, my mentor, said this.

958
01:11:02,263 --> 01:11:03,305
"Impossible

959
01:11:03,847 --> 01:11:05,849
is not a fact, it's an opinion."

960
01:11:08,227 --> 01:11:09,395
I see.

961
01:11:11,730 --> 01:11:13,732
You can do it, Soo-cheol.

962
01:11:13,816 --> 01:11:16,986
Take some blows for now
and become a champion in life.

963
01:11:17,069 --> 01:11:18,862
Did your mentor say that too?

964
01:11:18,946 --> 01:11:20,531
No, this is me talking.

965
01:11:20,614 --> 01:11:21,532
All right.

966
01:11:21,615 --> 01:11:22,658
Let's give it a try.

967
01:11:23,200 --> 01:11:24,034
Okay.

968
01:11:35,713 --> 01:11:36,755
Goodness.

969
01:11:36,839 --> 01:11:39,300
I didn't know you were relaxing
in such a beautiful

970
01:11:39,383 --> 01:11:41,218
and clean environment.

971
01:11:41,719 --> 01:11:42,928
Relaxing, my foot.

972
01:11:43,012 --> 01:11:44,430
How dare you come here?

973
01:11:44,513 --> 01:11:45,889
Mother, I invited her.

974
01:11:46,682 --> 01:11:47,975
Really? Why?

975
01:11:48,058 --> 01:11:50,185
There's something I haven't told you.

976
01:11:50,269 --> 01:11:52,104
It's about Grandfather's secret fund.

977
01:11:54,690 --> 01:11:56,025
Nine hundred billion?

978
01:11:56,108 --> 01:11:58,193
And that money is in Malaysia?

979
01:11:58,277 --> 01:11:59,820
No, I think it's here.

980
01:11:59,903 --> 01:12:00,904
-In Korea?
-Yes, sir.

981
01:12:00,988 --> 01:12:03,657
It was laundered in Hong Kong
before coming here.

982
01:12:03,741 --> 01:12:05,284
That paper company

983
01:12:05,367 --> 01:12:08,579
lent the money
to five investment companies in Korea

984
01:12:08,662 --> 01:12:10,539
before shutting down.

985
01:12:10,622 --> 01:12:14,084
That means the five companies
don't need to pay it back.

986
01:12:14,168 --> 01:12:16,295
Does Father own those companies?

987
01:12:16,378 --> 01:12:18,839
The ownership was transferred
before he collapsed

988
01:12:18,922 --> 01:12:20,257
to Ms. Moh.

989
01:12:20,716 --> 01:12:21,717
What did you say?

990
01:12:21,800 --> 01:12:23,927
Are you saying that bitch took it all?

991
01:12:24,011 --> 01:12:25,596
I don't think so.

992
01:12:26,180 --> 01:12:27,723
She's still looking for it.

993
01:12:36,440 --> 01:12:37,608
Tell me.

994
01:12:37,691 --> 01:12:38,692
Where's my money?

995
01:12:38,776 --> 01:12:41,695
Where's the secret fund that
you stashed away under my name?

996
01:12:41,779 --> 01:12:43,655
Are you sure Grace is allowed

997
01:12:43,739 --> 01:12:45,324
-to hear this?
-You can trust me.

998
01:12:45,407 --> 01:12:47,368
I've defected.

999
01:12:47,451 --> 01:12:48,660
Remember Lee Woong-pyung?

1000
01:12:48,744 --> 01:12:50,412
I've also flown my jet

1001
01:12:50,496 --> 01:12:53,040
to this land of freedom.

1002
01:12:53,123 --> 01:12:55,834
We'll see about that.
Let's take a look at your jet.

1003
01:12:55,918 --> 01:12:56,960
Tell us.

1004
01:12:57,044 --> 01:13:00,881
Someone I know in the real estate business
said something strange.

1005
01:13:00,964 --> 01:13:03,634
That Director Jin of Queens Gallery rented

1006
01:13:03,717 --> 01:13:06,345
a 5,000-pyeong warehouse
on the outskirts of Gyeonggi Province.

1007
01:13:06,428 --> 01:13:09,848
It's not like they're building a film set,

1008
01:13:09,932 --> 01:13:11,392
so why do they need such a huge one?

1009
01:13:11,475 --> 01:13:13,519
So you think the money is there.

1010
01:13:19,858 --> 01:13:22,152
You told me to bring you
all the mails sent

1011
01:13:22,236 --> 01:13:23,695
to the former chairman.

1012
01:13:23,779 --> 01:13:24,613
Good.

1013
01:13:30,744 --> 01:13:32,246
I could've come by myself.

1014
01:13:32,329 --> 01:13:34,623
You didn't have to swarm over here.

1015
01:13:34,706 --> 01:13:38,335
We can't trust you. It's like leaving
a kid to her own devices.

1016
01:13:38,419 --> 01:13:40,754
You were all exposed on the media.

1017
01:13:40,838 --> 01:13:43,882
-What if they recognize you?
-We disguised ourselves.

1018
01:13:43,966 --> 01:13:46,093
We'll take over from here, so you may go.

1019
01:13:47,219 --> 01:13:49,346
You're hurting my feelings.

1020
01:13:49,430 --> 01:13:52,099
This is an undercover mission.

1021
01:13:52,182 --> 01:13:54,476
Have you ever faked anything before? No.

1022
01:13:54,560 --> 01:13:56,854
My entire life has been fake,

1023
01:13:56,937 --> 01:13:58,981
so how could you leave me out of this?

1024
01:13:59,064 --> 01:14:00,983
Okay. Attention, please.

1025
01:14:01,608 --> 01:14:03,402
I'm a real estate agent,

1026
01:14:03,485 --> 01:14:06,780
and you're wholesale dealers
who need a huge warehouse.

1027
01:14:07,448 --> 01:14:10,492
I'll do the talking,
so don't say anything.

1028
01:14:13,162 --> 01:14:14,204
Let's go.

1029
01:14:18,500 --> 01:14:20,836
There's no place to stash all that money.

1030
01:14:21,378 --> 01:14:22,588
By the way,

1031
01:14:22,671 --> 01:14:23,755
what will they store?

1032
01:14:27,801 --> 01:14:29,303
-Golf clubs--
-Clothes--

1033
01:14:31,180 --> 01:14:32,598
He imports

1034
01:14:32,681 --> 01:14:34,892
golf equipment,

1035
01:14:34,975 --> 01:14:37,561
and she sells clothes in Dongdaemun.

1036
01:14:37,644 --> 01:14:39,855
He's from China.

1037
01:14:39,938 --> 01:14:42,357
He understands Korean

1038
01:14:42,441 --> 01:14:43,942
but can't speak it.

1039
01:14:45,861 --> 01:14:48,155
Sir. No coriander.

1040
01:14:48,989 --> 01:14:50,657
I don't speak Chinese.

1041
01:14:56,038 --> 01:14:58,582
Is the temperature and humidity in here

1042
01:14:58,665 --> 01:14:59,666
being regulated?

1043
01:14:59,750 --> 01:15:00,751
You noticed.

1044
01:15:00,834 --> 01:15:04,421
Our former customers
used to import artwork.

1045
01:15:04,505 --> 01:15:06,298
I know a bit about art.

1046
01:15:06,381 --> 01:15:07,466
Which artists?

1047
01:15:07,549 --> 01:15:09,510
They weren't famous.

1048
01:15:09,593 --> 01:15:11,637
They were rookies.
But they're very famous now.

1049
01:15:11,720 --> 01:15:13,931
Their works have jumped
20 to 30 times in price.

1050
01:15:14,014 --> 01:15:15,599
This place brings good energy.

1051
01:15:16,225 --> 01:15:19,269
-No cilantro in my dish, please.
-Yes.

1052
01:15:19,645 --> 01:15:22,064
He'd like to see the artwork.

1053
01:15:22,147 --> 01:15:22,981
Sure thing.

1054
01:15:23,065 --> 01:15:25,734
Your Majesty, what has become of my child?

1055
01:15:29,112 --> 01:15:30,572
The main door is open.

1056
01:15:30,656 --> 01:15:32,574
We're headed inside, so check the office.

1057
01:15:32,658 --> 01:15:34,576
Okay. I'll do that.

1058
01:15:48,382 --> 01:15:50,050
This is considered a business trip.

1059
01:15:50,133 --> 01:15:51,843
I'll pay you extra.

1060
01:15:53,512 --> 01:15:57,683
They really shouldn't catch me
doing this here.

1061
01:16:09,194 --> 01:16:12,656
This is the wrong way to store artwork.

1062
01:16:13,282 --> 01:16:16,326
Did you say these pieces
of artwork jumped in price?

1063
01:16:16,410 --> 01:16:18,328
Yes, that's what I heard.

1064
01:16:18,412 --> 01:16:22,416
I have a good eye for art,
but they don't look that great to me.

1065
01:16:27,588 --> 01:16:31,008
I think the money is in the artwork.
This is where he laundered it.

1066
01:16:31,091 --> 01:16:34,428
So he purchased the rookie artists' work
at a high price with the money?

1067
01:16:34,511 --> 01:16:36,388
Yes, by ten to twentyfold.

1068
01:16:36,471 --> 01:16:38,932
After wiring the money,
I think 90% or more of it

1069
01:16:39,016 --> 01:16:41,226
was given back to him via cash.

1070
01:16:41,310 --> 01:16:43,520
That's a substantial amount.

1071
01:16:43,604 --> 01:16:45,272
I wonder where all that money is.

1072
01:16:48,900 --> 01:16:50,027
DECRYPTING…

1073
01:16:55,449 --> 01:16:56,366
We need to leave.

1074
01:16:57,075 --> 01:16:57,909
We have no time.

1075
01:16:58,452 --> 01:16:59,494
Darn it.

1076
01:16:59,578 --> 01:17:01,121
There's too much data.

1077
01:17:04,875 --> 01:17:07,836
I'll ask my clients
and give you a call right away.

1078
01:17:09,546 --> 01:17:10,380
Goodbye.

1079
01:17:19,973 --> 01:17:21,725
OFFICE
PLEASE KNOCK

1080
01:17:26,813 --> 01:17:28,273
Is it broken?

1081
01:17:46,208 --> 01:17:49,419
You shouldn't get wet.
Wait here while I bring the car over.

1082
01:18:26,289 --> 01:18:27,374
Hae-in.

1083
01:18:36,925 --> 01:18:39,302
Hyun-woo, that was quick.

1084
01:18:40,804 --> 01:18:42,180
Why are you out here?

1085
01:18:42,264 --> 01:18:43,473
Get up.

1086
01:18:50,230 --> 01:18:51,148
I was a bit dizzy.

1087
01:18:52,524 --> 01:18:53,942
I'm hungry too.

1088
01:18:57,654 --> 01:18:59,906
Let's have something tasty
before we go home.

1089
01:19:03,785 --> 01:19:04,619
Sure.

1090
01:19:22,512 --> 01:19:23,472
Was I out for long?

1091
01:19:25,974 --> 01:19:27,350
No, not that long.

1092
01:19:37,027 --> 01:19:37,944
Hae-in.

1093
01:19:38,904 --> 01:19:40,071
Hang tight.

1094
01:19:41,072 --> 01:19:41,907
Why?

1095
01:19:42,574 --> 01:19:44,075
Are we being tailed again?

1096
01:19:44,159 --> 01:19:45,619
Don't worry. I can lose him.

1097
01:21:09,828 --> 01:21:11,288
-Are you okay?
-Yes.

1098
01:21:11,371 --> 01:21:13,206
Should we call the police?

1099
01:21:14,165 --> 01:21:15,417
-Wait.
-We should.

1100
01:21:15,500 --> 01:21:17,627
You were attacked
by three men last time too.

1101
01:22:56,226 --> 01:22:57,560
Hae-in!

1102
01:23:14,703 --> 01:23:15,537
Jeez.

1103
01:23:15,620 --> 01:23:17,288
Look at these comments.

1104
01:23:17,372 --> 01:23:18,665
This is because Eun-sung

1105
01:23:18,748 --> 01:23:21,209
spread false rumors about
how you were being investigated

1106
01:23:21,292 --> 01:23:23,336
for embezzling money prior to the divorce.

1107
01:23:23,420 --> 01:23:24,379
It's okay. Ignore them.

1108
01:23:24,462 --> 01:23:26,589
How can I possibly do that?

1109
01:23:26,673 --> 01:23:29,259
"Hong Hae-in's ex
must've married her for money."

1110
01:23:29,342 --> 01:23:30,218
"He's a scammer."

1111
01:23:30,301 --> 01:23:32,470
"This is why you should be wary
of handsome men."

1112
01:23:32,554 --> 01:23:34,723
How dare they curse at you?

1113
01:23:34,806 --> 01:23:36,057
Let's sue them all.

1114
01:23:36,141 --> 01:23:37,809
Forget it. Let's go.

1115
01:23:38,977 --> 01:23:41,021
Wait. Someone bad-mouthed Hae-in too.

1116
01:23:41,104 --> 01:23:44,232
"She already got a rebound
after the divorce. She must be easy."

1117
01:23:44,315 --> 01:23:46,026
They know nothing about her.

1118
01:23:46,109 --> 01:23:48,486
"Maybe she lied about dying."

1119
01:23:49,863 --> 01:23:51,322
This one crossed the line--

1120
01:23:53,283 --> 01:23:54,117
What's the ID?

1121
01:23:54,200 --> 01:23:55,076
Screenshot this.

1122
01:23:55,160 --> 01:23:56,953
Make a PDF file and sue them.

1123
01:23:57,037 --> 01:23:58,371
I won't settle or negotiate.

1124
01:23:58,455 --> 01:24:00,290
What's with your eyes? You're scaring me.

1125
01:24:00,373 --> 01:24:02,292
They will all pay for this.

1126
01:24:08,506 --> 01:24:11,342
QUEEN OF TEARS

1127
01:24:41,664 --> 01:24:43,917
I'm close to locating the secret fund.

1128
01:24:44,000 --> 01:24:45,835
That's it!

1129
01:24:45,919 --> 01:24:47,295
Snap out of it.

1130
01:24:47,378 --> 01:24:49,839
We have our own movie-like story.

1131
01:24:49,923 --> 01:24:52,092
How lovey-dovey.

1132
01:24:52,175 --> 01:24:54,594
Where is the statue?

1133
01:24:54,677 --> 01:24:55,512
Da-hye!

1134
01:24:56,137 --> 01:24:57,305
Scumbags!

1135
01:24:57,847 --> 01:24:59,140
I'd have to check.

1136
01:24:59,224 --> 01:25:01,226
I can't be sure of anything anymore.

1137
01:25:01,851 --> 01:25:04,145
It was me
who developed feelings for you first.

1138
01:25:04,229 --> 01:25:06,648
So he knows where the money is?

1139
01:25:06,731 --> 01:25:08,691
Is this real? Am I not dreaming?

1140
01:25:14,823 --> 01:25:16,825
Subtitle translation by Soo-ji Kim
